    <h2>Introduction: The Billionaire Landscape</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>The world's wealthiest individuals represent the pinnacle of entrepreneurial success and financial acumen.</li><li>Their fortunes are often tied to innovative technologies, strategic investments, and global market dominance.</li><li>This presentation explores the top 10 richest individuals, their sources of wealth, and their impact on the world.</li><li>Data is based on Forbes' Real-Time Billionaires List (as of October 26, 2023) and may fluctuate.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">2/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 3 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>1. Elon Musk: The Visionary Entrepreneur</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $235 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Tesla, SpaceX, X (formerly Twitter)</li><li>Key Achievements: Revolutionized the electric vehicle industry, pioneered reusable rocket technology, and acquired a major social media platform.</li><li>Philanthropy: Musk Foundation focuses on renewable energy, human space exploration, and AI safety.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">3/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 4 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>2. Bernard Arnault & Family: The Luxury King</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $211 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: LVMH (Moët Hennessy Louis Vuitton)</li><li>Key Achievements: Built LVMH into the world's largest luxury goods conglomerate, owning brands like Louis Vuitton, Dior, and Tiffany & Co.</li><li>Business Strategy: Focuses on acquiring and nurturing iconic luxury brands, emphasizing craftsmanship and exclusivity.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">4/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 5 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>3. Jeff Bezos: The E-Commerce Pioneer</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $151 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Amazon</li><li>Key Achievements: Founded Amazon, transforming online retail and cloud computing.</li><li>Current Focus: Blue Origin (space exploration), The Washington Post, and philanthropic endeavors through the Bezos Earth Fund.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">5/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 6 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>4. Larry Ellison: The Oracle of Databases</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $144 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Oracle</li><li>Key Achievements: Co-founded Oracle, a leading database software company.</li><li>Investments: Holds significant stakes in Tesla and other technology companies. Known for his passion for sailing.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">6/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 7 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>5. Bill Gates: The Software Mogul Turned Philanthropist</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $111 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Microsoft</li><li>Key Achievements: Co-founded Microsoft, revolutionizing personal computing.</li><li>Current Focus: Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, addressing global health, poverty, and education.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">7/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 8 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>6. Warren Buffett: The Oracle of Omaha</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $107 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Berkshire Hathaway</li><li>Key Achievements: Built Berkshire Hathaway into a diversified holding company through value investing.</li><li>Investment Philosophy: Focuses on long-term investments in companies with strong fundamentals and sustainable competitive advantages.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">8/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 9 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>7. Mark Zuckerberg: The Social Media Architect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $99 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Meta Platforms (Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp)</li><li>Key Achievements: Co-founded Facebook, connecting billions of people worldwide.</li><li>Current Focus: Metaverse development, artificial intelligence, and expanding Meta's reach.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">9/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 10 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>8. Larry Page: The Search Engine Innovator</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $96 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Google (Alphabet)</li><li>Key Achievements: Co-founded Google, revolutionizing internet search and online advertising.</li><li>Current Role: Board member and controlling shareholder of Alphabet Inc.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">10/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 11 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>9. Sergey Brin: The Algorithm Architect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $93 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Google (Alphabet)</li><li>Key Achievements: Co-founded Google, transforming information access and technology.</li><li>Current Role: Board member and controlling shareholder of Alphabet Inc.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="slide-number">11/13</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 12 -->
<div class="slide">
    <h2>10. Michael Dell: The PC Pioneer</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Net Worth (Approx.): $73 Billion</li><li>Source of Wealth: Dell Technologies</li><li>Key Achievements: Founded Dell, revolutionizing the personal computer industry through direct sales and customization.</li><li>Business Strategy: Focuses on providing end-to-end technology solutions for businesses and consumers.</li>
    </ul>
